19:22 PM
1. data.ts had a typo of size but i had laid out everything as sizes
2. Pexels.com image download failing FileSystem.downloadAsync sends no browser headers so Pexels blocks it with a timeout. 
The real fix was to just store the Pexels URL directly in the database for seed data, uploading to your own storage only
matters when real users upload their own images. Still pexel is constantly block image request, for future i'll add a cloudinary
or imgur as alternative but for now I added imageURLs in appwrite database.
3. isSelected causing row rejection a ui aiding property that is added at time of rendering i mistook it as a 
required database entry but that was easy to spot.I learnt appwrite rejects the entire row if you pass an attribute that
doesn't exist in the schema — it doesn't just ignore unknown fields, this made the error look like menuItemId was
missing even though it wasn't. 
4. Finally reseeding was successfull
### Rule only pass attributes that exist in the Appwrite schema.
5. While rendering images from URL, add headers of referer as pexels blocks hotlinking

